<div class=""><br class="">
</div>
How's this:
<div class=""><br class="">
</div>
<div class="">- Brian Barrett and myself were the primary maintainers of LAM/MPI.</div>
<div class="">- Brian and I moved on to Open MPI about a decade ago.</div>
<div class="">- There have been no releases of LAM/MPI in many years.</div>
<div class="">- There won't be any future releases of LAM/MPI, ever.</div>
<div class="">- There is zero support for LAM/MPI.</div>
<div class="">- Open MPI has MUCH better support for run-time systems and modern networks.<br class="">
<div class="">- Open MPI has an active developer and user community.</div>
<div class="">- Open MPI is supported by multiple different vendors.</div>
<div class="">- Jeff Immelt wants you to move away from LAM/MPI.</div>
